* Focus: These states have little to no specific AV legislation and are relying on existing common law or have initiated research task forces.
* The Gap: These are the jurisdictions where the first major A2A collision will create the most unpredictable legal outcome, as there is no legislative or executive guidance whatsoever.
The key takeaway is that no US state has yet legislated a functional, technical standard that resolves the financial subrogation crisis of A2A collisions. The ACS Framework provides the ready-made model legislation required to bridge this national regulatory gap.


